==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thwack
<hw>Thwack</hw> <pr>(thw⟦acr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Thwacked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Thwacking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
OE. <ets>thakken</ets> to stroke, AS. <ets>⟦thorn⟧accian</ets>, E.
<ets>whack</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To strike with something flat
or heavy; to bang, or thrash: to thump.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A distant
<xex>thwacking</xex> sound.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>W. Irving.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To fill to overflow.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Stanyhurst.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thwack</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Thwack
<hw>Thwack</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A heavy blow with something flat or
heavy; a thump.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With many a stiff <qex>thwack</qex>, many a bang,⟦br⟧
Hard crab tree and old iron rang.</q> <rj><qau>Hudibras.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thwaite</ent>⟦br⟧
